07261nam a22010935i 9783110955286DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20141996gw     fo  d z      fre d  a97831109552867 a10.1515/97831109552862doi  a(DE-B1597)45572  a(OCoLC)979786408  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 afre  agwcDE 7aLAN0090002bisacsh04a440  aID 51502rvk0(DE-625)rvk/54799:00aDépendance et intégration syntaxique :bSubordination, coordination, connexion /cClaude Muller.  aReprint 2014 1aTübingen : bMax Niemeyer Verlag, c[2014] 4c©1996  a1 online resource (337 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aLinguistische Arbeiten ,x0344-6727 ;v3510 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aCe volume est le produit d'un colloque international tenu à Bordeaux en 1994. Les contributions, produites par quelques-uns des meilleurs spécialistes internationaux de linguistique du français et d'autres langues, sont centrées sur le problème central de l'organisation de l'énoncé, entre les relations de dépendance et l'intégration en unités syntaxiques. On y trouvera un fidèle panorama des développements des recherches actuelles en syntaxe, sémantique, mais aussi en pragmatique des énoncés longs et des connecteurs. C'est dire qu'il intéressera non seulement les linguistes et les grammairiens, mais aussi les analystes du discours et de l'argumentation.  aThis volume is the fruit of an international colloquium organized at Bordeaux in 1994. The papers stem from some of the most renowned experts on the syntax of French and other languages, and centre around the central problem of the organisation of utterances between dependency relations and integration into syntactic units. The discussion faithfully mirrors the latest research developments in the syntax, semantics and pragmatics of extended utterances and connectors. It is thus of interest not only to linguistics and grammar specialists but also to scholars working in the field of discourse analysis and argumentation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aLinguistics and SemioticsxLanguages of EuropexLatin and Romance LanguagesxFrench. 0aLinguistics and SemioticsxLevels of Linguistic AnalysisxSyntax. 4aFranzösisch. 4aHypotaxe. 4aKoordination ‹Linguistik›. 4aWortverbindung. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAllaire, Suzanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndersen, Hanne Leth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnscombre, Jean-Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBanys, Wieslaw, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerthonneau, Anne-Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlumenthal, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoone, Annie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorillo, Andrée, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCamus, Rémi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChevalier, Gisèle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCombettes, Bernard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoulomb, Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFauci, Nunzio La, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeigenbaum, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForsgren, Mats, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFugier, Huguette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaatone, David, 